verbose_text: Thus, it can be concluded that overexpression of DNAM-1 on NK-92 cells directly increased degranulation and cytokine prodcution against in vitro propagated primary sarcoma explants bearing CD112 and/or CD155, while healthy PBMCs were minimally affected.
